President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 16 through May 22, 2015, as National Safe Boating Week. This proclamation emphasizes the importance of protecting America's waterways and ensuring the safety of boaters and passengers. The proclamation encourages individuals to prepare for potential hazards by checking the forecast, filing a float plan, performing safety checks on their vessels, and ensuring they have essential safety equipment. It also emphasizes the need to be prepared for sudden weather changes and to never drink while boating. The proclamation recognizes the efforts of the United States Coast Guard in keeping Americans safe at sea. It encourages everyone to visit www.USCGBoating.org to learn more about responsible boating practices. The proclamation concludes by stating that the Congress has authorized the President to annually proclaim the 7-day period prior to Memorial Day weekend as National Safe Boating Week.